SUMMARY:Artist Spotlight - Finding Figurative: The Human Form at the Rental Sales Gallery
DESCRIPTION:Join us for the first in our new series of Artist Spotlight shows. In Finding Figurative\, we will be celebrating 12 of our artists who create works inspired by the human form. Showcased works are all part of the Gallery’s inventory\, and will be available for rental or purchase.Featuring pieces by Paula Bullwinkel\, Brian Cameron\, Jennifer Gillia Cutshall\, Richard Cutshall\, Helday de la Cruz\, Scott Erwert\, William Hernandez\, Stacy Lovejoy\, Karen Wippich\, Mitch Wolfsehr\, Haelyn Y\, and Michelle Yamamoto. Learn more at rentalssalesgallery.com. \n\n\n\nThe opening reception is on Friday\, March 6\, from 4-7pm
URL:https://portlandartmuseum.org/event/artist-spotlight-finding-figurative-the-human-form-at-the-rental-sales-gallery/
LOCATION:Rental Sales Gallery\, 1237 SW 10th Ave\, Portland\, 97205\, United States
CATEGORIES:Free & discounted
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://portlandartmuseum.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/RSG-FF-The-Lurking-Loss-of-Innocence-Michelle-Yamamoto.jpg
END:VEVENT
